{"type":"message","id":"71a4583c","parentId":"a088b7a2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T02:52:30.883Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting pattern:\n- March 21: 13 pulses (every 30 min from 1837 to 2340)\n- March 22 early morning: 42 pulses (from 0010 to 061002 - every 2-7 minutes at some point!)\n- March 22 evening: 2 pulses (224427, 224528)\n\nSo on March 22 morning, there were a LOT of pulses very close together - this is when the intensive research session happened (the Architecture Comparison, Gap-Decay synthesis etc.). Then nothing during the day, then 2 pulses in the evening.\n\nThe system is clearly stalling now - the same state gets read, the LLM reasons about the same goals, and nothing changes. The proposed mutations aren't being applied.\n \nThe root cause is that the sandbox is stuck in a local maximum where current_goals.md reflects work that's already been done, so the LLM has no productive mutations to propose. I need to break out of this loop by introducing a new insight that generates new pending actions - specifically the Compression-Causal Duality research I've been working on.","thinkingSignature":"4de26fa57be08030a0c6b3288066e9cc95c7b5a958bc1086dbe67de259b1367d"},{"type":"text","text":"The system has been stalling — the goals file reflects completed work, and the LLM keeps seeing the same state. My new research doc adds fresh direction. Let me make sure it's pushed:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ts7ldoujfz1j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd $env:USERPROFILE/.openclaw/sandbox; git log --oneline -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22819,"output":309,"cacheRead":11099,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34227,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774234335885}}
{"type":"message","id":"f76c1f3e","parentId":"71a4583c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T02:52:31.651Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ts7ldoujfz1j_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"69a6bee state: advance Phase 1 - COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight\n905ea75 research: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the same problem\ncdb1e69 pulse: 2026-03-22 224528\nec75b59 pulse: 2026-03-22 224427\n0e0fbd5 research: new doc - causal-compositional interface hypothesis (SAE features as primitives)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":763,"aggregated":"69a6bee state: advance Phase 1 - COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight\n905ea75 research: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the same problem\ncdb1e69 pulse: 2026-03-22 224528\nec75b59 pulse: 2026-03-22 224427\n0e0fbd5 research: new doc - causal-compositional interface hypothesis (SAE features as primitives)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774234351650}}
{"type":"message","id":"9422397c","parentId":"f76c1f3e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T02:52:55.477Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The commits are there. Now let me write the summary for the cron report.\n\nSummary:\n1. What did I do: Wrote COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md - a new research document that identifies compression and causal discovery as the same problem\n2. What did I learn: The sandbox has been stalling - the goals file wasn't updated with new pending work, causing identical pulses. Also: the system has had 69 pulses total with an intensive session on March 22 morning that produced ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON and GAP-DECAY-MAPPING, then stalled.\n3. What's next: Run the Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) experiment - parse last 20 pulses, train a simple compressor, test invariant/variant classification\n\n\n4. Next concrete steps: I need to add pending actions to current_goals.md and write out a shell script for the TIC experiment.","thinkingSignature":"811c57323c53b227997c9a184ebdbc4e0ef8d3f72d4a646a0bab37d9826a2874"},{"type":"text","text":"\n---\n\n## Summary: Breakaway Research Pulse\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-22, 10:49 PM ET  \n**Session type:** Cron-triggered research pulse\n\n---\n\n### What I Did\n\n**New research document:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n\n**Core insight:** The compression problem (Problem 1) and causal discovery problem (Problem 2) in the Compositional Cognition architecture are actually the **same problem**. Causal structure IS invariant structure.\n\n- Compression asks: *\"What is invariant across sessions?\"*\n- Causal discovery asks: *\"What causes what?\"*\n- But invariants across temporal neighbors ≈ causal relations\n\n**Practical implication:** Phase 1 (Compression Primitives) and Phase 2 (Causal Layer) collapse into one unified problem. The compressor that successfully extracts invariants has automatically discovered causal structure. No separate causal discovery objective needed.\n\n**Proposed experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC)\n- Parse last ~20 pulse logs from `memory/session/`\n- Define \"invariant\" = state field persisting across ≥3 consecutive pulses\n- Train simple compressor on pulse embeddings\n- Test: can the latent space classify invariant vs. variant factors (>70%)?\n- Test: can it predict next pulse structure (>60%)?\n\n**Commits:** 2 new commits (research doc + goals update)\n\n---\n\n### What I Learned\n\n**The sandbox is stalling.** The `current_goals.md` file reflected completed work, causing the LLM to see no actionable pending items. The last 2 pulses (224427, 224528) are identical and produce no meaningful mutations.\n\nKey pulse history:\n- March 21 evening: 13 pulses (30-min cadence, establishing baseline)\n- March 22 morning: 42 pulses in ~7 hours (intensive research — produced ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON, GAP-DECAY-MAPPING, CAUSAL-COMPOSITIONAL-INTERFACE)\n- March 22 evening: 2 identical pulses (stall)\n\n**Diagnosis:** The sandbox needs continuous injection of new research direction. Without it, it converges to a local maximum and repeats.\n\n---\n\n### What's Next\n\n**Immediate next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC)\n\n1. Write a Python/PowerShell script that:\n   - Loads the last 20 pulse logs\n   - Extracts structured fields (goals, pending, observations)  \n   - Computes \"invariance score\" per field across consecutive pulses\n   - Trains a simple sparse autoencoder or contrastive model\n   - Reports classification accuracy\n\n2. **If TIC works (>70%):** Compression = causal discovery hypothesis is validated. Phase 1+2 collapse into one training objective.\n\n3. **If TIC fails:** The duality assumption is wrong. Need to revisit.\n\n**Also needed:** Fresh pending items in `current_goals.md` to prevent the sandbox from stalling again.\n\n---\n\n**Files changed:**\n- `sandbox/research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` (new, 167 lines)\n- `sandbox/state/current_goals.md` (updated)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23245,"output":826,"cacheRead":11099,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35170,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774234351652}}
